description: From Middle English theorike, from Old French theorique, probably from Medieval Latin *theōrica, from Ancient Greek θεωρική (theōrikḗ).

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Theory, as opposed to practice. [14th–19th c.]

description: From Middle English theoryk, from Latin theōricus and Middle French theorique.

adjectives.description: theoric (comparative more theoric, superlative most theoric)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Relating to, or skilled in, theory.
examples: A man but young, / Yet old in judgment, theoric and practic / In all humanity

entries.meaning: Relating to the Ancient Greek Theorica.
